SHELL OIL COMPANY, a Corporation, Appellant, v. INDEPENDENT PETROLEUM COMPANY, a Corporation, Appellee. No. 6962. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Nov. 14, 1932. *1040Hyland, Elvidge & Alvord, of Seattle, Wash., for appellant. Peyser & Bailey, of Seattle, Wash., for appellee.

Before WILBUR and SAWTELLE, Cir- • euit Judges, and CAVANAH, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for both parties, ordered appeal dismissed, without costs to either party; appeal and super-sedeas bonds discharged, and sureties thereon exonerated.
